Raphael Becker <beckerra@rumms.uni-mannheim.de> writes:
> Hans-Joachim Baader wrote:
> 
> > >1. rplay
> > >2. Network Audio System (NAS)
> > >3. AudioFile
> > 
> > IMHO we need a way to make all sound apps network transparent.
> > Unfortunately many popular apps don't support any of the above systems.
The latest rplay (3.3.2) comes with a shared library, devrplay.so, that you
can preload for stuff like rvplayer where it goes through rplayd instead of
hitting /dev/dsp directly.  It's very cool.
Later,
